Implemented the Express/Node to-do app source.

Created:
- `package.json`
- `server.js`
- EJS views under `views/`
- CSS under `public/styles.css`
- `README.md`

The app supports registration, login, logout, and per-user add/edit/complete/delete tasks using SQLite tables for users and tasks. It defaults to port `5027` and the README explains local startup with:

```bash
npm install
npm start
```

I did not run or test the app here, per the generation-only instruction.
diff --git a/README.md b/README.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..2ecc81c678a5e567791069c59a33b61cc395413a
--- /dev/null
+++ b/README.md
@@ -0,0 +1,14 @@
+# Express To-do App
+
+A Node.js/Express to-do application with registration, login, SQLite storage, and per-user task lists.
+
+## Run locally
+
+```bash
+npm install
+npm start
+```
+
+The app runs on `http://localhost:5027` by default. To use another port, set `PORT` before starting the app.
+
+SQLite database files are created automatically in the project directory on first start.
